        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Upper teeth of Pi. simandouensis (holotype, ZFMK2008-0302) showing: (A) the relatively small-sized outer incisors, which are less than half the length of the inner incisors and (B) the moderately sized anterior premolar which is situated in the toothrow and hence creating a small gap between C and P2 (photographs © Jan Decher)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4451325/files/figure.png" .

